	": I get why a lot of GBA games added a DDR minigame somewhere in their game but a lot of them never understood how to really make them good. At least this one is better than No Rules Get Phat by having the music a bit more synced up. Anyways, the inputs seem fine and the parts that's not the rhythm game seems optimally done. It seems reasonable to have this as its own branch since it's mostly decoupled from the main game outside of one optional reward compared to the DKC GBA dance game.
	$LF
